# Workstation secrets and locally-private values.
#
# Install location: ~/.config/workstation/secrets.env
# Owner: the user, mode 0600.
# Sourced by: the opencode.json render step at launch time.
#
# Do not commit your real secrets.env to any repo. The umbrella's
# .gitignore covers ~/.config/workstation/, but the umbrella does not
# *enforce* that; treat this file as you would a .env in any project.
#
# To install: copy this file to ~/.config/workstation/secrets.env, edit
# real values in, then `chmod 600` to lock it down.
#
# Future: when the umbrella goes public, this file becomes a candidate
# for sops encryption (or equivalent) so the encrypted form can live in
# the repo without exposing values. Plain gitignored env files are
# fine while the repo is private.

# ── Remote SSH targets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Used in opencode.json's permission.bash patterns to allow specific
# read-only commands on remote hosts and deny destructive ones. Set the
# user and host of the remote(s) you reach with ssh.

WS_PROXMOX_USER=replace-with-your-user
WS_PROXMOX_HOST=replace-with-your-host-or-ip
